cons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>Yesterday: my first time in umbral planes. We're there with a single group checking it out.  We had done a few pulls and were getting the hang of that, and I had floated out to look around. I go into the middle and see all the dark assassins and hte dark masters. I comment on the dark master and gulp since he was an even con.<br><br>XX tells the group &quot;Pull him <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> &quot;<br><br>She was kidding. I did it anyway. Tagged him from range, when the roamers had gone by. Took the 1000 point HT. Only had one assassin add who was stabbing me silly. Hit Escape. Changed my angle, re-tagged the master, ran back to the zone, avoiding all the mobs in the way, and brought him home, single pull.<br><br>Of course then it took us ten minutes to kill him. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p><hr align="center" size="1"> <center><IMG SRC="http://www.logalt.net/upload/osprey-sig.jpg"><BR> <A HREF = "http://www.silentsentinels.com"; TARGET = "_blank">Silent  Sentinels -- Come See Us</A> <BR>A.K.A. Kayleigh Silverwing, Templar of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukronx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kronx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:10:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22771.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Times when you love being a rogue</span><hr size=1> Got my level 1 rogue in the Tower of Frozen Shadow...<br><br>Was on a guild raid in the Hole. Scaley was all alone and we decided we couldn't take him, so we gather for a screenshot or two. An imp pops and scaley aggros whatever he aggros. Both groups go down fast, but I manage to camp my tank. Eventually I log back in to take the death and get summoned. Of course, the rogue is hiding comfortably and just hits his Thurg gate potion while Scaley tears out my innards.<br><br>Two tanks, cleric and same rogue fighting in Wurms in GD much earlier. Things go bad and the other tank goes down. When I'm at half health the cleric says OOM. As I go down, the rogue hits a backstab which causes the wurm to run. Being the only member left alive, he finishes off the wurm with little problem.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Please read our sig/personal pic rules. - ShadowCross</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadowcross.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowcross</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/13/02 2:29:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umuuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Muuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:23:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22771.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Times when you love being a rogue</span><hr size=1> Ya know, I never get tired of those stories, Kronx <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Muuk<br>49 rogue<br>Zeb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulonghairedwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Longhairedwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:29:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22771.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Times when you love being a rogue</span><hr size=1> I thank the Powers That Be everytime I step into a zone and hit my stealth keys. Then watch as a massive train comes storming thru. As the mobs go calmly past looking for someone else to chase screaming to the zone I hit my rogue LFG key.<br>I am also pretty sure that a few people I've grouped with were glad I was rogue when I have told them to consent me so I could drag thier corpse to the nearest cleric and save them the run,boat ride and wait for spireport from point A to point Z.<br>I don't even mind to much anymore that I often get asked to do corpse drags for people I'm not grouped with at the moment. I feel that we are somewhat of a forgotten class on the higher end game. So these little reminders of rogue usefulness are good for them. I find it rather disconserting to BS for 250 or so and have someone compelment me on a good hit, when it's barely 1/2 of what I can do with a single hit. <br>Amalice Sa'Dath <br>Guildleader Bane of Tunare<br>58th Grandmaster Rogue<br>Tunare server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=argyllmacguinness>Argyll MacGuinness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 7:56:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22771.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Saved the day..</span><hr size=1> Two stories, both in the Plane of Hate.<br><br>On my very first PoH raid (aside from my solo book run) we were setting up the usual CoH break. We got a cleric camped at the west wall, but the mage died somewhere on south wall and the rest of the break group didn't even make it past the zone-in house. Second try - all dead on zone-in. Argyll tells the guild, &quot;Port me up alone.&quot; Fifteen minutes later we were starting pulls. Between that and finding the puller who got summoned to someplace on 2nd floor, I'm not sure my guild would let me sit out on a Hate raid.<br><br>Many raids later, I was with another guild in Hate. They were calling reinforcements in to drop Inny. A couple groups make it in okay, then a wizard dies porting up. At this point I'm the only rogue. &quot;Ugh,&quot; I say, &quot;somebody sow me.&quot; I dragged a wizard corpse from the zone-in house to somewhere along the west wall of 2nd floor. Not 10 seconds after I get the wizard corpse back to camp, two stragglers die at zone-in. &quot;Ugh,&quot; I say, &quot;somebody refresh my sow.&quot; I get back with those two corpses and the puller dies. Seconds later, the ranger they sent to get the puller's corpse (made no sense to me either) dies. So I go get their corpses. I've a feeling the raid leader was extremely glad she let me port up late.<br><br>Man, I love the Plane of Hate. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unardacofeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nardac of EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 11:39:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicI